      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm working on a shopify theme and im having a weird issue with the product template. on desktop it looks fine but when i check it on my phone the product image is totally overlapping the title and description. cant tell if its a padding issue or something with the media queries. \n\nhere is the css for the product section:\n\n.product-container {\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: row;\n  gap: 20px;\n}\n\n.product-media {\n  width: 50%;\n}\n\n.product-info {\n  width: 50%;\n}\n\n@media only screen and (max-width: 767px) {\n  .product-container {\n    display: block;\n  }\n  .product-media, .product-info {\n    width: 100%;\n  }\n}\n\nthe liquid looks standard too. can u see what might be causing the overlap?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, it seems like the product image and the title/description are getting too close for comfort on mobile devices. The issue might be due to the gap between them. When the screen size is smaller, the gap might not be enough to separate the two elements. Try adjusting the gap value in your CSS to give them a bit more breathing room. \n\nHere's an example:\n\n```css\n.product-container {\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: row;\n  gap: 30px; /* Increased gap value */\n}\n```\n\nAnd if that doesn't work, you could try adding some padding to the product-info element to create some space between the image and the title/description. \n\n```css\n.product-info {\n  width: 50%;\n  padding: 10px; /* Added padding */\n}\n```\n\nI hope this helps! Let me know if you need any more assistance.",
